    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-09-25T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-09-25T12:00:00-05:00" n="847"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d847">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867.24/424a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-09-25T13:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 25, 1942—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>465. With reference to the Department’s 461 of September 23, 5 p.m., our
                    prospective needs for the funds required for an extensive preemptive program in
                    Turkey, and the substantial quantities of wheat which the Turks appear hopeful
                    of providing the bottoms to lift leads the Department to the conclusion that it
                    would be a mistake to grant on any basis other than cash reimbursement wheat
                    over and <pb facs="0750" n="738" xml:id="pg_738"/> above the two lots totaling
                    21,000 tons which Lend-Lease, at your request, is providing for non-cash
                    reimbursement. The Department believes it would be well, therefore, to
                    discourage any hopes the Turks might nurture for large quantities of wheat from
                    the U. S. without making immediate payment either in dollars or Turkish
                    pounds.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
